  "text": "In the k-Connectivity Augmentation problemĜ contains a spanning (k − 1)-connected subgraph of cost 0. A feasible solution for the k-Connected Subgraph problem can be obtained by solving sequentially ℓ-Connectivity Augmentation problems for ℓ = 1, . . . k, but this reduction usually invokes a factor of H(k) in the ratio, where H(k) denotes the k-th harmonic number. Several ratios for k-Connected Subgraph were obtained in this way, c.f. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The currently best known ratios for the general and the augmentation version, for both directed and undirected graphs, are summarized in Table 1 .",
